cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on using radiomics, a high-dimension imaging feature set, to predict lung cancer using CT imaging data. This involves image analysis and feature extraction, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a deep convolutional neural network learning architecture to realize custom radiomic sequencers. This involves machine learning techniques for training and optimizing the neural network. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses AI techniques such as deep learning to predict lung cancer from CT imaging data. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves retrieving information from CT imaging data to predict lung cancer. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with analyzing and processing multimedia data in the form of CT imaging data to predict lung cancer.
